Terminologies and Coding Standards in Brazilian PHC

CIAP stands for Classificação Internacional da Atenção Primária, Portuguese for International Classification of Primary Care.
We used ICPC-2, which is the version currently in use by the Brazilian Primary Health Care System.

CID stands for Classificação Internacional de Doenças, Portuguese for International Classification of Disease. We used ICD-10 version 2008, which is the version currently in use by the Brazilian Primary Health Care and Brazilian National Surveillance systems.

ABP is the coding scheme adopted for annotating the reason of encounter in Brazilian Primary Health Care facilities with no Electronic Health Record in place.
